<dl id="un1013ai"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013ai"> (NLI.3) 13(ai)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Christ&apos;s bride sister the moistening of light, born of virgin, repentant Sophia. <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un1013ai"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/lexk.htm#un1013ai">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/k86.htm#un1013ai">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/k86.htm#un1013ai">1986 (9.68)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/l22k.htm#un1013ai">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#un1013ai">MS NLI.8A-003</ms> </li><li><a name="k11d" href="../udra/u9da.htm#k11d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/k/k11d.htm#un1013ai">Draft: 9.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">A Study in Christian Gnosticism&rdquo; 331: &ldquo;So He <font color="green">[the Christ]</font> emanated and descended to His own <mark>Sister <font color="green">[and Bride]</font>, the Moistening of Light</mark> <font color="green">[i.e., Light in the realms of the Ocean of Genesis]</font>. <br>And she the Downward Sophia <font color="green">[that is, Wisdom tending downwards to genesis, or manifestation, or matter]</font>, becoming conscious that her Brother was descending to her, both proclaimed His Coming through John, and made ready the Baptism of Repentance, and adopted Jesus beforehand <font color="green">[that is, chose him as their Son]</font>; so that the Christ descending might find a pure vessel <font color="green">[sc., <mark>born of the Virgin or Repentant Sophia</mark>]</font> &hellip;&rdquo; <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#thrdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. Mead, &ldquo;The Secret of Jesus</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="un1014b" href="un1all.htm#un1014b">UN1 (NLI.3):014(b)</a> below. </mm> </dd></dl>
